>
  <article class="prose prose-slate dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
    <h1>Examples</h1>

    <p>
      Here are some real-world examples to help you get started with gsheetbase.
    </p>

    <h2>Example 1: Todo List Manager</h2>
    <p>Create a simple todo app backed by Google Sheets:</p>
    <pre><code class="language-javascript">{`// Fetch all pending todos
const todos = await db.query()
  .select('id', 'title', 'due_date')
  .where('status', '=', 'pending')
  .orderBy('due_date', 'ASC')
  .get();

// Mark a todo as complete
await db.update(todoId, { status: 'complete' });

// Add a new todo
await db.insert({
  title: 'My new task',
  status: 'pending',
  created_at: new Date()
});`}</code></pre>

    <h2>Example 2: User Directory</h2>
    <p>Query and manage a user directory:</p>
    <pre><code class="language-javascript">{`// Search for users by name
const users = await db.query()
  .select('name', 'email', 'department')
  .where('name', 'LIKE', '%John%')
  .get();

// Get users from a specific department
const salesTeam = await db.query()
  .where('department', '=', 'Sales')
  .orderBy('name', 'ASC')
  .get();

// Update user info
await db.update(userId, {
  department: 'Marketing',
  updated_at: new Date()
});`}</code></pre>

